pr_review_body:
Thanks all!
I'll go ahead merge this now.

@rmlarsen I'll import this into the Google env asap.

@vcarpani Thanks for the changes. Apologies it took me a bit to review but I was on my annual leave.

I left one more comment to ensure we follow the same patterns as on the rest of the code-base. This is not just a matter of styling but also to ensure that the solution aligns with other building systems that are used internally at Meta. Once you have it, to be on the safe side, I think it's also worth it for us to test it internally and confirm that nothing breaks. Give me a shout when ready and I'll do this for you.

Again thanks for the contribution and apologies for the long delay.

This seems to work very smoothly with the metric-alarms 👍 🎉
I think the Scheduler has everything we need 😄 

@thrau: Should we merge it to master then, or should I include it in the PR for the metric-alarms?

@simontindemans Thanks a lot for all your help with this contribution! I appreciate you sticking with it through all the feedback. This change looks great, especially for first-time contributor, and it'll be really helpful for other users facing the same challenges you faced.

Please let us know if you have any other features you'd like to see or contribute to the project. Thanks again for helping develop of Ray!

By the way, you can also stay in touch with the Ray community through our [Slack](https://forms.gle/9TSdDYUgxYs8SA9e8) or the [Discuss forum](https://discuss.ray.io/). Feel free to reach out there as well!

@manabuishii impressive work tracking down where you had to add the state/job info :clap: 

I think what this change is doing is making the job info from the parent Job available to children Jobs. Not sure if there's any downsides to this.

**Maybe** another approach could be to modify `Process#evalResources` and rewrite the Resource value, evaluating the expression to `4`. This way when children Job are created they wouldn't have to try to resolve the variables/values.

@pb-new-username: Left you some comments/feedback. Specifically, I don't believe we can use DataFrames since there are no headers. perhaps you have a working example. Also have a comment on expected data. 

I like this call though. We should see if there's some way of getting into the details of a specific day as to not have to load the entire year. Look forward to chatting.

Also. Saw you have a PR against my branch (rsforbes) and this branch (swar), is this the same PR? perhaps you can open this against main since Live was merged. Just a thought.

Thanks for the patch!  Unfortunately, both these files are generated code, and would need fixing up in their [source template](https://github.com/googleapis/gapic-generator-python/blob/master/gapic/templates/scripts/fixup_%25name_%25version_keywords.py.j2), rather than in this repository.

The whitespace and `lambda` fixes should be trivial to do there:  the `cst.Element` one, however, is apparently gnarly:  @software-dov has a comment there referring the the "log chipper" formatting which happens.

@busunkim96, @parthea could we perhaps run `black` over the `scripts/` directory via `owlbot.py` to make these fixes in place?
